  "read": "The standard-EP top2 hot-expert branch has real modeled row-movement opportunity: the no-threshold timing run sees median modeled max-load relief of 13.81% and mean relief of 14.37%, with about 73.95k remote-hot rows per call on average. But the current implementation does not convert that into higher e2e throughput. Adding a min-reduction gate at 10% skips about one third of candidate execute calls and lowers peak logged memory by about 4.01 GiB, but step-2 throughput drops slightly from 7,455 to 7,448 tok/GPU/s. Decision: keep the threshold as an opt-in diagnostic/lower-overhead knob, not a promoted branch. The next hot-expert optimization needs more than selection filtering: reduce hot-weight broadcast/reduce overhead, record actual executed hot rows, and compare against the stronger MORI/AITER stage1_recompute_cached12 baseline."
